# Words data model

## Word entity

A **Word** is the core entity. Each word belongs to a single `learningLanguage` (the language it is written in). A word can have translations/meanings to multiple languages.

```
Word
├── _id (UUID)
├── origin ("hello", "table", "courir")
├── nativeLanguage ("en", "fr")
├── transcription ("həˈləʊ")
├── audio { _id, url }
├── frequency (float, higher = more common)
├── description (English definition)
├── etymology (word history)
├── isDeleted (bool)
│
├── meanings
│   └── { lang: { value: [translations], isVerified: bool } }
│       e.g. { "ru": { "value": ["привет", "алло"], "isVerified": true } }
│
├── translations
│   └── { lang: { pos: "translation" } }
│       e.g. { "de": { "noun": "Gruß", "interjection": "Hallo" } }
│
├── translationList
│   └── { lang: [ { _id, text, pos, isDefault, isSpecific } ] }
│       Detailed translations with IDs and flags
│
├── examples ["There is dinner on the table."]
├── localizedExamples
│   └── [ { _id, origin, translations: { ru: "..." }, wordForm, pos, start, end, audio } ]
│
├── synonyms      [ { _id, origin } ]
├── antonyms      [ { _id, origin } ]
├── formalSynonyms    [ { _id, origin } ]
├── informalSynonyms  [ { _id, origin } ]
│
└── confusedWords
    └── { linkedWords: [{_id, origin}], pos, difference: [str], whenToUse: str }
```

## Key concepts

### Meanings vs Translations

- **`meanings`** — simplified: `{ "ru": { "value": ["стол"], "isVerified": true } }`. Flat list of meaning values per language.
- **`translations`** — grouped by POS: `{ "de": { "noun": "Tisch", "verb": "tischen" } }`. One string per POS.
- **`translationList`** — full details: each translation has an `_id`, `text`, `pos`, `isDefault`, `isSpecific`. Use this for precise analysis.

### Determining context / sense of a word

For polysemous words (e.g. "building"), look at `translationList`:
- `pos: "noun"` → the building (здание)
- `pos: "verb"` → building something (строительство)

Each sense has `isDefault: true/false` and `isSpecific: true/false` to identify the primary meaning.

### confusedWords

Contains words commonly confused with this one:
- `linkedWords` — the other words (with IDs so you can look them up)
- `difference` — array of explanation strings
- `whenToUse` — guidance on correct usage

### Coverage analysis

To check translation coverage, iterate over `meanings` or `translationList`:
- Count languages where data exists
- Check `isVerified` to separate verified from unverified
- Missing language = no key in the object

### Linking words to exercises (cross-service)

EWA exercises reference words by `_id`. When analyzing course content:
1. Get exercises via `ewa-courses` tools
2. Extract word IDs from vocabulary exercise data
3. Batch-fetch word data via `Get_words_by_IDs`
